Login and Home Page Scripts
  This repository contains scripts for a basic web application, 
  including a login page and a home page. The provided scripts are intended to demonstrate a simple login mechanism and a basic home page structure.

Table of Contents
  Installation
  Usage
  Folder Structure
  Dependencies
  Contributing
  License

Usage
Start the Development Server: If you have a local server setup, start it to serve the files. 
For example, using Live Server in VSCode, you can right-click on index.html and select "Open with Live Server."

Access the Application: Open your web browser and go to http://localhost:PORT (replace PORT with the appropriate port number if needed).

Login Page:

Navigate to login.html to view and test the login functionality.
Enter your credentials to log in (default credentials may be specified in the script or documentation).
Home Page:

After logging in, you'll be redirected to the home.html page.
This page will display a basic structure and can be modified as needed.

Folder Structure
/your-repository
│
├── login.html        # HTML file for the login page
├── home.html         # HTML file for the home page
├── login.js          # JavaScript file for login page functionality
└── home.js           # JavaScript file for home page functionality


Dependencies
HTML5
JavaScript (ES6+)
No external libraries or frameworks are required for the basic functionality. However, you may choose to integrate additional libraries or frameworks as needed.

Contributing
Contributions are welcome! If you have suggestions or improvements, please follow these steps:

Fork the repository.
Create a new branch (git checkout -b feature-branch).
Make your changes.
Commit your changes (git commit -am 'Add new feature').
Push to the branch (git push origin feature-branch).
Create a new Pull Request.
